DDNS (nsupdate) reporter
by Tomas Hlavacek (tmshlvck@gmail.com)

Requirements for client:

Python 3.2+
nsupdate & dig utils

apt-get install knot-dnsutils

Prepare the server config - example for Knot 2.4.0:

1) Install Knot

apt-get install knot

2) generate TSIG key:

keymgr tsig generate test

3) put into config file (/etc/knot/knot.conf) the following content:

server:
    identity: ""
    version: ""
    user: "knot:knot"
    listen: [ 0.0.0.0@53, ::@53 ]

control:
    listen: "knot.sock"

log:
  - target: stderr
    any: warning

  - target: syslog
    any: info

key:
  - id: key_d_domain
    algorithm: hmac-md5
    secret: "xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"

acl:
  - id: acl_update_d_domain
    address: [0.0.0.0/0, ::/0]
    key: key_d_domain
    action: update

zone:
  - domain: "d.domain.cz."
    file: "/var/lib/knot/d.domain.cz.zone"
    acl: acl_update_d_domain

4) On the client run
```
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/tmshlvck/ddns/master/deploy.sh
chmod a+x deploy.sh
./deploy.sh <hostname> <domain> <server> '<TSIG KEY>'
```
i.e.
```
./deploy.sh eagle d.taaa.eu krtek.taaa.eu 'hmac-sha256:key_d:xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx='
```

Alternative manual procedure: 

4a) Fill TSIG password to the server & client config. Move the reportipconf.py to /etc/ddns/

5a) Start Knot and test the reportip.py on the client. Move the reportip.py to /usr/local/sbin/ .

6a) (Optional for NetworkManager) Put the file 99dnsupdate into /etc/NetworkManager/dispatcher.d/ and make it executable.

7a) (Optional) Put the following line to /etc/crontab

*/39 *  * * *   root    /usr/local/sbin/reportip.py >>/var/log/dnsupdate.log

